title: This oil refiner is cutting 1,100 jobs — and giving billions of dollars to its shareholders
description: Phillips 66 is cutting at least 1,100 jobs by the end of this year as the refining giant seeks to slash costs and steer a larger chunk of its soaring profits to shareholders.

title: Haiti's cholera death toll rises to 136 as outbreak gets 'worse and worse every day'
description: A deadly resurgence of cholera in Haiti has claimed 136 lives so far, according to the Caribbean nation's health ministry.

title: Indian diamond billionaire Nirav Modi loses appeal against extradition from UK
description: A London court on Wednesday rejected an appeal from Indian billionaire Nirav Modi against his extradition from the United Kingdom to India to face charges of fraud and money laundering.

title: British nurses to hold first ever strike over pay
description: Tens of thousands of British nurses will go on strike for the first time over demands for better pay, their trade union said on Wednesday, adding to pressure on Prime Minister Rishi Sunak during an economic crisis.

title: Chocolate is having a moment
description: Between warnings of a recession, high inflation and layoff fears, the news is bleak. Why not have some chocolate?

title: Changes are coming to Wordle
description: Changes are coming for Wordle ... again.

title: Elon Musk sold nearly $4 billion worth of Tesla stock since Twitter deal closed
description: Elon Musk sold $3.95 billion worth of Tesla stock since completing his purchase of Twitter late last month.

title: Magnitude 5.7 earthquake shakes Italy's Adriatic coast
description: A strong earthquake of magnitude 5.7 struck off Italy's Adriatic coast early on Wednesday, but caused no serious damage or injuries, according to initial reports.

title: Killing of Pakistani journalist in Kenya was 'targeted' attack, minister says
description: A Pakistani journalist shot dead by police in Kenya last month was the victim of a "targeted killing," a senior member of Pakistan's government said on Tuesday, without offering any evidence to support his claim.
